News

  • 2022/07/29: The cell-type terms as well as associated taxonomy IDs of cell populations in scRNA-seq studies are updated.
  • 2022/07/21: By manual inspection of curation result, the redundant cell types are further deprecated, and the cell types added in up-to-date Cell Ontology are updated.
  • 2022/05/25: The panel of cell-type distribution across tissues is added.
  • 2022/05/21: Four large-scale human single-cell atlas from Human Cell Atlas Consortium are incorporated containing datasets Tabula Sapiens Consortium, Eraslan et al., Domínguez Conde et al. and Suo et al..
  • 2022/04/20: The mouse single-cell atlas of Tabula Muris Consortium containing nearly 100,000 cells from 20 tissues is incorporated.
  • 2022/03/21: The search function in home page is updated to enable searching cell types by synonym.
  • 2022/03/10: The browse pages are updated to be more straightforward.
  • 2022/03/07: The manual curation of 31,647 records containing 797 cell types, 3,351 cell markers, 20 species, 184 tissues and 157 conditions are added.
  • 2022/02/30: Manual curation of 677 publications out of 2,317 recent single-cell relevant publications is finished.
  • 2022/01/11: The information of cell surface marker is added.
  • 2021/12/10: The assessment function for cell markers is added to highlight high-quality cell markers.
  • 2021/11/06: The summary panel is added for each cell type, cell marker and tissue.
  • 2021/10/06: The cell markers from OnClass are added.
  • 2021/09/06: The cell markers from Human Cell Landscape are added.
  • 2021/09/05: The panel of “conserved cell marker” is added enabling cross-species comparison.
  • 2021/09/03: The orthologous information of cell markers is added.
  • 2021/09/02: The pages of species and conditions are updated.
  • 2021/05/20: Cell Taxonomy is available online.
